PHP Authentication & Role Management System
A secure, lightweight authentication system built with PHP and MySQL. Features include secure password hashing, session management, and role-based access control.

Features:
Secure Registration: Passwords are encrypted using password_hash().

Safe Login: Uses Prepared Statements to prevent SQL Injection.

Session Security: Implements session_regenerate_id and httponly cookies.

Role-Based Access: Distinguishes between user and admin roles.

Modern UI: Clean, industrial design with a #b6b6b6 primary color theme.

Responsive Design: Works on both desktop and mobile.

Installation & Setup

1. Database Configuration:
Open phpMyAdmin.

Create a new database named auth_system.

Run the following SQL to create the users table:

CREATE TABLE users (
id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL UNIQUE,
password VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
role ENUM('user', 'admin') DEFAULT 'user',
created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

2. File Setup:
Move the project folder to your local server directory (e.g., C:/xampp/htdocs/auth-system/).

Update config/db.php with your database credentials if they differ from the defaults:

